headlines.description: Cyril Langevine scored a career-high 14 points and added eight rebounds in 22 minutes off the bench on Friday night to help No. 18 Rhode Island beat Davidson 72-59 and tie a school record with its 15th win in a row.

headlines.description: Tre'Shaun Fletcher scored 18 points and grabbed 12 rebounds, Nate Navigato had three 3-pointers and 19 points and Toledo defeated Miami (Ohio) 73-67 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Fletcher has double-double to lead Toledo to 73-67 win

headlines.description: Stone Gettings had 23 points and 10 rebounds and Cornell rolled to 78-60 victory over Brown on Friday night.

video.headline: Cornell tops Brown, 78-60  - Via Ivy League

headlines.description: Miye Oni made five 3-pointers in scoring 17 points and Yale defeated Columbia 88-84 on Friday night to snap a two-game skid.

headlines.description: AJ Brodeur had 20 points and 10 rebounds and Pennsylvania closed on a 13-6 surge and held off Dartmouth 64-61 on Friday night for its fifth straight win.
headlines.shortLinkText: Penn holds off Dartmouth 64-61, remains undefeated in Ivy

video.headline: Penn edges Dartmouth, stays undefeated in Ivy play  - Via Ivy League

headlines.description: Christian Juzang scored a career-high 20 points and Harvard defeated Princeton 66-51 on Friday night for the Crimson's fifth victory in their last six games.
headlines.shortLinkText: Juzang scores career-high 20 points in Harvard's 66-51 win

headlines.description: Devonte Green and Juwan Morgan each scored 19 points Friday night, leading Indiana to an 80-56 blowout over Minnesota.
headlines.shortLinkText: Indiana blows out Minnesota 80-56 for 2nd straight win

headlines.description: Trey Moses scored 22 points, Tahjai Teague had 20 points and 14 rebounds and Ball State cruised to an 87-68 victory over Kent State on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Moses, Teague lead Ball State over Kent State 87-68

headlines.description: Kendrick Nunn scored 21 of his 28 points in the second half to help Oakland beat Detroit Mercy 87-78 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Nunn scores 28, leads Oakland over Detroit Mercy 87-78

headlines.description: Nate Sherwood scored 23 points, and Victor Sanders blocked a shot at the buzzer to give Idaho a 66-64 victory over Eastern Washington on Friday night.

nowFeed.headline: Oklahoma's Trae Young, on his recent offensive struggles: "Im getting guarded like nobody else in the country is being guarded, scouted on like no one else in the country. Its a mystery coming out each and every game to try and figure out how a team is going to guard me and how Im going to dictate how my team wins.  Its a lot tougher for me to score now than it was in the beginning. ... Its a process. Right now, its tough."
